description: Recently sold: $173,500. This classic Duluth home on the hill has a beautiful year-round view of Lake Superior and the boats coming and going at an affordable price. Built in 1914, this home retains its original woodwork, such as 10-inch baseboards and maple hardwood floors throughout the first floor. There have also been a variety of modern updates for your convenience, such as a large, sunny kitchen with a bay window and newer dishwasher (2012), deck on the first floor, window seat and balcony on the second floor, and a two-car garage with attic storage. Enjoy closets in each of the bedrooms (the master has two, including a walk-in!), walkout basement, large front porch and the cherry tree blossoms in June. The roof and direct vent water heater were replaced in 2008, a sump pump was installed in 2009, and the sewer system from the main stack in the basement out to the alley has been replaced within the past five years. Located within walking distance to several playgrounds, Chester Park, and downtown, this home is clean and ready for someone who appreciates craftsmanship, convenience, and watching the sun rise over the lake.
Recently sold: $197,000.
